@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Terms of Service";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
<p class="text-muted"><em>Last updated: May 2026</em></p>

<p>
    Welcome to FindActivity. By creating an account or using the service, you agree to these Terms.
    If you don't agree, please don't use FindActivity.
</p>

<h2>1. Who can use FindActivity</h2>
<ul>
    <li>You must be at least 18 years old.</li>
    <li>You must provide accurate information when you sign up, including your real date of birth.</li>
    <li>You're responsible for keeping your account credentials safe and for everything that happens under your account.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. Activities and content</h2>
<p>
    You can create activities ("events") and join activities created by others. Activities and any content you post must
    follow our <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="CommunityGuidelines">Community Guidelines</a>. You retain
    ownership of what you post, but you grant us a non-exclusive license to display it on FindActivity for the purpose
    of operating the service.
</p>

<h2>3. Free service</h2>
<p>
    FindActivity is free to use. There is no charge for creating an account, hosting an activity, or joining one.
    We don't process payments and we don't allow paid events at this time.
</p>

<h2>4. Geographic scope</h2>
<p>
    FindActivity currently serves the Greater Seattle area. Activities should take place within or near this area.
    We may reject activities that fall outside our supported region.
</p>

<h2>5. What you agree not to do</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Don't post or organize anything that's illegal, sexual, harassing, hateful, violent, or that endangers minors.</li>
    <li>Don't spam, scrape, or use automated tools against the service.</li>
    <li>Don't impersonate another person, or misrepresent your affiliation with anyone.</li>
    <li>Don't use FindActivity to promote a business, sell goods or services, or recruit for paid work.</li>
    <li>Don't try to bypass our security, age verification, or moderation systems.</li>
</ul>

<h2>6. Reports and moderation</h2>
<p>
    Users can report activities or other users. We review reports and may remove content, suspend, or terminate
    accounts that violate these Terms or our Community Guidelines, with or without notice.
</p>

<h2>7. Off-platform conduct</h2>
<p>
    Activities happen in the real world. Use good judgment when meeting people you found on FindActivity. We are not
    responsible for the conduct of any user, on or off the platform, or for the safety of any activity. Participate
    at your own risk.
</p>

<h2>8. Disclaimers and limitation of liability</h2>
<p>
    The service is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. To the fullest extent permitted by law, we are
    not liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the service.
</p>

<h2>9. Termination</h2>
<p>
    You can delete your account any time. We can suspend or terminate accounts that violate these Terms or our
    Community Guidelines. On termination, the rights you grant us in your content end, except to the extent
    necessary to retain legal records or anonymize already-public content.
</p>

<h2>10. Changes to these Terms</h2>
<p>
    We may update these Terms. We'll update the "Last updated" date above and, for material changes, notify you
    in the app or by email. Continued use of FindActivity after changes means you accept the new Terms.
</p>

<h2>11. Governing law</h2>
<p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Washington, USA.</p>

<h2>12. Contact</h2>
<p><a href="mailto:hello@findactivity.local">hello@findactivity.local</a></p>

